    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness, then heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a clean plate to rest (save the pan!)</p><p>Add your <strong>white</strong> <strong>long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>in a small bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>ginger paste</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>garden veg mix</strong>, <strong>cooked rice</strong> and <strong>gochujang sauce </strong>to the pan with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/gochujang-chicken-fried-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> cooked chicken</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>gochujang fried rice </strong>and top with the <strong>sliced chicken</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>black</strong> <strong>sesame seeds </strong>and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
